{
  "text": "Scots pine bark extract has been shown to have high antioxidant activity in the methyl linoleate model [CITATION_1] , high antimicrobial activity against Staphylococcus aureus [CITATION_2] , and it contains compounds that inhibit the production of two proinflammatory mediators, nitric oxide and prostaglandin E2 [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Scots pine phloem aqueous methanol extract has been shown to be antimicrobial against S. aureus, one of the most common bacteria causing food poisoning [CITATION_5] . Further, the extract showed slight inhibiting activity against Escherichia coli and the yeast Candida albicans [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22888581",
